Vice President Biden met with Afghan President Ashraf Ghani and Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif to discuss the relaunch of peace talks between the Afghan government and the Taliban. The Vice President offered condolences for recent terrorist attacks in both countries and commended both leaders for their diplomatic efforts. He reaffirmed U.S. support for reconciliation and improved bilateral ties between Afghanistan and Pakistan, emphasizing their importance for regional stability. The Vice President encouraged both leaders to remain committed to a credible peace process, which includes reducing violence, eliminating militant safe havens, and promoting bilateral cooperation.